## Cloudflare Workers + Static Assets — exclusion list
##
## Anything matched here is NOT uploaded as a static asset, so it doesn't
## count toward the 25 MiB-per-asset limit and doesn't get served publicly.
## Same glob syntax as .gitignore.

# Dependency tree (workerd alone is ~118 MiB and breaks the upload)
node_modules/

# VCS / scratch
.git/
.wrangler/
.claude/
.tmp/
.tmp_*
*.log

# Local-only data and secrets
images/raw/
data/maker-contacts.json
.env
.env.*

# Internal docs that should not be served publicly
CLAUDE.md
PRODUCTS.md

# Admin hub — kept out of the public deploy until Cloudflare Access is
# configured per admin/CF_ACCESS_SETUP.md. Remove this rule AFTER Step 8
# of the runbook (gate verified working). Until then, /admin/* must
# return 404 from the public site.
admin/

# Lock files — no need to ship
package-lock.json
bun.lock
bun.lockb
